{{Quote|Mon Mothma of Chandrila and Senator Leia Organa of Alderaan have been positively identified as key figures in the Rebel Alliance command hierarchy. This treasonous crime against the Empire is punishable by death, and those so accused and at large are automatically placed on the Imperial Remandation List.|An Imperial HoloVision report|<ref name="Galaxywide">{{JournalCite|4|Galaxywide NewsNets}}</ref>}}
The '''Imperial Remandation List''' was a list of individuals wanted by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. Individuals identified as leaders of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]], such as [[Senator/Legends|senators]] [[Mon Mothma/Legends|Mon Mothma]] and [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]], were sentenced to [[Death/Legends|death]] and placed on the list. The Imperial Remandation List was mentioned in an [[Imperial HoloVision]] report published<ref name="Galaxywide" /> in [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]].<ref name="Galaxy NewsNets date">The [[Imperial HoloVision]] report in {{JournalCite|4|Galaxywide NewsNets}} states that it takes place on 35:9:1 of the [[Great ReSynchronization]] calendar, which corresponds to [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]] per the reasoning [[Template:YearMathGRS|here]].</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The Imperial Remandation List was mentioned in the [[Galaxywide NewsNets]] section written by [[Paul Sudlow]] and published in the [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 4|the fourth issue]] of the ''[[Star Wars Adventure Journal]]'' magazine, which was published by [[West End Games]] in [[November]] of [[1994]].<ref name="Galaxywide" />

